The paper discusses the concept of conflict in information fusion, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The theory of belief functions, which is the main focus of the paper, is also related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes approaches to manage conflict, which can be seen as a problem in social informatics (cs.SI).
